The paper deals with timing synchronization in a digital communication system, specifically in the context of TDS-OFDM for DTMB standard. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of frequency-domain response for timing synchronization, which is a signal processing technique, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Signal and Image Processing (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the bit-error-rate (BER) effect of sampling clock phase offset, which is a statistical measure, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
